This branch is made on top of the neighbour_client_server branch
Rebase your work on top of this before pushing.
this can be done using

git fetch --all
If you have uncommitted work: git stash
git rebase origin/neighbour_client_server
And, if you used stash: git stash pop
now push your changes.

How I've built and run the database during development
in message-forwarder/src/test/docker/db
docker build -t interchanges_test .
docker run -it -e POSTGRES_USER=federation -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=federation -e POSTGRES_DB=federation -p 7070:5432 --name interchange_container interchanges_test

If you want more rows in the database, add the sql insert statements in the data.sql file.

Next, we need two Interchanges to forward messages between. 

To build the "local" IXN, do:
in message-forwarder/src/test/docker/localIxn
docker build -t local_ixn .

and to run:
docker run --rm -it -p 8080:8080 -p 5671:5671 -p 5672:5672 --name local_ixn local_ixn

To build the "remote" IXN, do:
in message-forwarder/src/test/docker/remoteIxn
docker build -t remote_ixn .

and to run:
docker run --rm -it -p 8081:8080 -p 6671:5671 -p 6672:5672 --name remote_ixn remote_ixn
	


